learning_outcomes.en:
Upon completion of the course, students will: 

- understand the European legal integration, the constitutive elements of the EU acquis; and legislative roles of the EU institutions; 

- analyse the main sources and principles of EU law, their implementation in the practice and their relation to other general principles of law; 

- understand and make distinction between different actions in the Court of Justice of the EU; choose the right remedy for a practical case; understand the procedural aspects and interpretation methods of the COJEU; 

- analyse a judgment of the COJEU and solve a case in the framework of the basic course according to the given questions/methodology.
